27/04/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU Committee of Permanent Representatives decided on Wednesday (26 April) to launch negotiations with Croatia and Turkey on the Education and Culture chapter of the acquis. Letters were sent to both candidate countries, inviting them to submit their negotiation positions on the chapter. 
Poland meanwhile reaffirmed its support for Croatia's accession to the EU and NATO. During Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader's visit to Warsaw on Wednesday, Polish counterpart Kazimierz Marcinkiewicz said his country stands ready to assist Zagreb. (Vecernji list - 27/04/06; HINA - 26/04/06)
